You need to find the value of $m \times n$, where $m$ and $n$ are the expressions for $x$ and $y$. (\textit{See triangle sum}Post #1054 for triangle sum.)</think>
<answer>By the \stackrel{~}{\textbf{fact~}} \textit{that opposite sides of a parallelogram are equal in length}, we have
\begin{align*}
AB&=CD\\
38&=2x+4\\
2x&=34\\
x&=17
,\end{align*}
and
\begin{align*}
AD&=BC\\
24&=3y^3\\
3y^3&=24\\
y^3&=8\\
y&=2
,\end{align*}
so \[
x\times y=\boxed{34}
.\end{align*}
</answer>

